,Recommended,256330,8339982,"Posted: 27 December, 2013",all,Iggy Koopa,"It's difficult to really compare WRC 4 to anything; it's so much more realistic than DiRT 3, it's so much more exciting than DiRT 1, it's so much newer than Colin McRae Rally, and, well, I don't have any experience rallying in real life. I guess its biggest competitor is DiRT 3, so let's get to it.WRC 4 is exactly what you'd expect it to be: a game that closely and faithfully follows the workings of the World Rally Championship 2013 season. The tracks are diverse and aplenty and the cars and teams are all in the WRC. They're limited to the 2013 season, which is kind of a bummer, but unlike DiRT 3, you getallof the 2013 cars with all of the liveries, as opposed to just a couple cars per class with a couple more that you have to pay for.Now you might be thinking, ""this all seems very serious, does this mean the cars are super-realistic and hard to control?"" And that's just the thing: the driving physics are realistic buteasyto control, and you can change around the options to make it even easier. Due to being designed for the console market, it's been made very accessible to be played by everyone; it's like theForzaof rally games. Whereas DiRT 1 - the most realistic modern rally game I've played - is a total buzzkill with its constant grip and lack of a sense of speed, WRC 4 makes it feel like you're going really fast and barely in control, and at any point it can throw in a chicane and hairpin out of nowhere to make you spin even a front-wheel-drive car.And that's not even the best part. The best part is that this game makes you try hard not to crash. In DiRT 3, it doesn't really matter if you crash, because it takes a lot to do any mechanical damage and the weekends are so short that it'll be auto-repaired before long anyway. The first time you skid into a wall in WRC 4, on the other hand, you'll swear to yourself not to let it happen again. Crashing has more consequences in this, and you'll find yourself repairing even the most minor damage in the service park at the end of each day, and--...Okay, I'm gushing, so I should wrap this up. WRC 4 is afreaking great gameand you should buy it if you think DiRT 3 wasn't as good as it could have been, or if you just want something a little exciting."
