,Recommended,256330,13947428,"Posted: 11 January, 2015",all,plasot,"Altough graphics are somehow oudated, game itself bring some nice arcade rallying fun. For first time from ages (and I mean ages, Mobil 1 Rally Championship I think was last rally game with some part of license) we got official FIA licence which helps build rally mood, we got original WRC drivers in original cars battling on four WRC orignal levels. There is something like career mode which will guide you trough all four levels of World Rally Championship from Junior WRC to the top. Locations are official WRC sites but Milestone didn't recreate stages but simply make some variation about it keeping national character. Stages are disappointingly short, max 6km on one stage and 6 stages on one rally which gives us merely 25-30km of rallying on each locations. But stages are packed with action, so we still got fun twitching fingers on endless hairpins. To be not mistaken - this is not a simulator, stages are too short and setups too basic, but game itself could pretend to title of semi-simulator in which nicely done arcade parts like steering, setups or maps got added a pinch of simulation in physics and handling. There are some bugs, mostly in collssion detection and in handling but cautious driver could ride trough whole rally didn't noticing any part of it. Graphics are moderate, cars looks good, some stages also looks nice but some stages looks like unfinished (maybe they will finish it in console game Sebastian Loeb Rally Evo).Concluding - really nice rally rcade game with pinch of simulation reminding last rally oriented CMR game - Colin McRae 2005 (in first Dirt on 56 events only 18 were rally oriented with next 6 hill climbs)."
